The paper deals with the Internet routing protocol BGP and its vulnerabilities to routing anomalies such as route leaks and interception attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses formal languages to represent the global routing system, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the need for monitoring and detecting these incidents, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
